article.description: — Jalen Slawson posted 17 points and seven rebounds as Furman narrowly defeated Samford 71-68 in the semifinals of the Southern Conference tournament on Sunday night.
article.headline: Slawson, Furman beat Samford 71-68 in SoCon tourney semis
article.linkText: Slawson, Furman beat Samford 71-68 in SoCon tourney semis
article.story: ASHEVILLE, N.C. -- — Jalen Slawson posted 17 points and seven rebounds as Furman narrowly defeated Samford 71-68 in the semifinals of the Southern Conference tournament on Sunday night. Mike Bothwell had 17 points for Furman (22-11). Conley Garrison added 10 points and five steals. Ques Glover had 23 points for the Bulldogs (21-11). Jermaine Marshall added 22 points and 12 rebounds. Jaden Campbell had 14 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
